==Ancient Greek==

===Etymology===
From [[Indoeuropean|IE]] ''kwon-'', cognate with [[hound]], {{lat}} [[canis]], {{deu}} [[Hund]].

===Pronunciation===
*{{italbrac|Classical}} {{IPA|/ky̌ɔ̂ːn/}}
*{{italbrac|Koine}} {{IPA|/ˈkuon/}}

===Noun===
{{grc-noun|κυνός|m & f|third|kyōn|κυων}}

# [[dog]]
# [[bitch]] (in both technical and pejorative senses)
# offensive person

====Inflection====
{{grc-decl-3rd-ln|κύων|κυν|κύν|κυ|VS=κύον}}

====Usage notes====
The alternate forms [[κύων]] (vocative singular) and [[κύνεσσι]] (dative plural) also exist.

